b'\n          About ACCC        '
b'The Academic Computing and Communications Center provides central computer support to the UIC campus community. Our major services include network, wireless and internet connectivity; Blackboard, public labs, classrooms, and instructional technology; digital and analog telephony; email, calendar, emergency communications, accounts and passwords, and other business tools. For a full list of services and details, consult the Service Catalog.'
b'Service Catalog'
b'Mission'
b'To be a source of competitive advantage and value for the University of Illinois by providing a wide range of information solutions and services to the University\xe2\x80\x99s campuses, operating units, and external stakeholders.\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0 \xc2\xa0'
b'ACCC and UIC'
b"ACCC works closely with UIC's Provost and her office,\xc2\xa0 the campus IT Governance Committees appointed by the Provost, the faculty senate Academic Services Committee, and the Student Fee Advisory Committee. At the university level, we work with the University Technology Management Team, the Committee for Architecture and Vision, and several organizations on other campuses."
b'campus IT Governance Committees'
b'faculty senate Academic Services Committee'
b'University Technology Management Team'
b'Committee for Architecture and Vision'
b'At the campus unit level, ACCC works with REACH, a group of departmental representatives each appointed by a department head.\xc2\xa0 REACH members often provide technical support to departments as part of their duties.\xc2\xa0 The connection between ACCC and REACH lets us coordinate services and information, and helps keep us informed about departmental needs.\xc2\xa0 We also coordinate with Phonebook Contacts (PB Contacts), who maintain information about people, affiliations and NetIDs in the UIC directories.\xc2\xa0 To find your REACH or PBContact representative, search for your department in the UIC Departments A-Z list.'
b'REACH'
b'UIC Departments A-Z list.'
b'Organization'
b'ACCC is currently headed by our Director and has 7 internal groups:'
b'Network Engineering &Telecommunications Services'
b'Services Delivery: General Service Desk support\xc2\xa0and specialized support including learning technologies, learning environments, desktop support, On-site Support, the C stops, and the Academic Multimedia Lab; incident\xc2\xa0and knowledge management.Community Engagement and Innovation: Instructional Design Office; learning systems integration and administration; communication and outreach functions, including all publicly facing digital content; client statistical analysis; professional development.Administrative Operations: Student workforce management and ACCC assets coordination.'
b'Major Communications'
b'If you have specific computer support questions, please contact us.'
